Imputation of Missing Values, Scaling, and Centering: Training Set

# if categorical feature: replace missing value with most common feature value
# if numerical feature: replace missing value with the mean of the column 
# setting the reference groups of categorical variables to the most frequent groups of variables

train <- read.csv("ckd_data_train.csv")
attach(train)

test <- read.csv("ckd_data_test.csv")

age[is.na(age)] <- mean(age, na.rm = T)
train$blood_pressure[is.na(train$blood_pressure)] <- mean(train$blood_pressure, na.rm = T)

train$specific_gravity[is.na(train$specific_gravity)] <- 1.02
train$specific_gravity <- factor(train$specific_gravity, ordered = FALSE)
train$specific_gravity <- relevel(train$specific_gravity, ref = "1.02")

train$albumin[is.na(train$albumin)] <- 0
train$albumin <- as.factor(c(0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5))

train$sugar[is.na(train$sugar)] <- 0
train$sugar <- as.factor(train$sugar)

train$red_blood_cells[is.na(train$red_blood_cells)] <- "normal"
train$red_blood_cells <- as.factor(train$red_blood_cells)
train$red_blood_cells <- relevel(train$red_blood_cells, ref = "normal")

train$pus_cell[is.na(train$pus_cell)] <- "normal"
train$pus_cell <- as.factor(train$pus_cell)
train$pus_cell <- relevel(train$pus_cell, ref = "normal")

train$pus_cell_clumps[is.na(train$pus_cell_clumps)] <- "notpresent"
train$pus_cell_clumps <- as.factor(train$pus_cell_clumps)

train$bacteria[is.na(train$bacteria)] <- "notpresent"
train$bacteria <- as.factor(train$bacteria)

train$blood_glucose_random[is.na(train$blood_glucose_random)] <- mean(train$blood_glucose_random, na.rm = T)

train$blood_urea[is.na(train$blood_urea)] <- mean(train$blood_urea, na.rm = T)

train$serum_creatinine[is.na(train$serum_creatinine)] <- mean(train$serum_creatinine, na.rm = T)

train$sodium[is.na(train$sodium)] <- mean(train$sodium, na.rm = T)

train$potassium[is.na(train$potassium)] <- mean(train$potassium, na.rm = T)

train$hemoglobin[is.na(train$hemoglobin)] <- mean(train$hemoglobin, na.rm = T)

train$packed_cell_volume <- as.numeric(train$packed_cell_volume)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
train$packed_cell_volume[is.na(train$packed_cell_volume)] <- mean(train$packed_cell_volume, na.rm = T)

train$white_blood_cell_count <- as.numeric(train$white_blood_cell_count)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
train$white_blood_cell_count[is.na(train$white_blood_cell_count)] <- mean(train$white_blood_cell_count, na.rm = T)

train$red_blood_cell_count <- as.numeric(train$red_blood_cell_count)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
train$red_blood_cell_count[is.na(train$red_blood_cell_count)] <- mean(train$red_blood_cell_count, na.rm = T)

train$hypertension[is.na(train$hypertension)] <- "no"
train$hypertension <- as.factor(train$hypertension)

train$diabetes_mellitus[is.na(train$diabetes_mellitus)] <- "no"
train$diabetes_mellitus <- as.factor(train$diabetes_mellitus)

train$coronary_artery_disease[is.na(train$coronary_artery_disease)] <- "no"
train$coronary_artery_disease <- sapply(train$coronary_artery_disease, function(x) gsub('\\s+', '', x))
train$coronary_artery_disease <- factor(train$coronary_artery_disease, ordered = FALSE)

train$appetite[is.na(train$appetite)] <- "good"
train$appetite <- as.factor(train$appetite)

train$pedal_edema[is.na(train$pedal_edema)] <- "no"
train$pedal_edema <- as.factor(train$pedal_edema)

train$anemia[is.na(train$anemia)] <- "no"
train$anemia <- as.factor(train$anemia)

train$class <- sapply(train$class, function(x) gsub('\\s+', '', x))
train$class <- as.factor(train$class)

# scaling and centering the numerical variables in the training set
train[c(1, 2, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18)] <- lapply(train[c(1, 2, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18)], function(x) scale(x, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE))
